axies can be\naccounted for with a HCN abundance of ~10^{-6} (relative to H2) and luminosity\nsurface brightness in the range (0.5-2)x10^{8}$ Lsun pc^{-2}, predicting a\nfar-infrared photosphere with Tdust}~80-150 K --in agreement with the values\ninferred from far-infrared molecular absorption.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Aug 2019 09:10:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-25"}
